sec.p:
A comparison of capacitive performance was performed using galvanostatic charge/discharge curves at a constant current density of 500 mA/g, which is shown in Fig. 5b. It is clearly seen that the shape of the charge/discharge curves of varied films are closely triangular in shape, indicating a good reversibility during the charge/discharge processes. The discharge times of the PEDOT-PSS/RGO nanocomposite films are longer than that of the pure PEDOT-PSS and pure RGO films, suggesting the coating of the PEDOT-PSS on the RGO surface greatly extending the discharge time. Moreover, the PS/RG 1:1 film shows the longest charge/discharge time, indicating the largest specific capacitance of these electrode films. The specific capacitance can be calculated from the capacitance equation:Cm=iΔtmΔV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
